I was nearby and wanted to find a place to try out. I browsed Yelp and found this place. The name caught my eye because someone mentioned this place recently to me.  This restaurant is small - about eight tables. You go up and order & pay for your food, then find a table. They have real plates and silverware, which is nice.  I had a cheese enchilada with red sauce - home made, not out of a can - and you can tell. I tried both al pastor and carne asada street tacos, which were quite tasty as well.  I would recommend checking this place out! They are friendly as well. I want to try the green sauce - that'll have to wait til next time.

